Nigerian music star, Timaya, has threatened to beat up fellow celebrity, Ubi Franklin. The singer issued a warning to the music executive in what seemed to be a personal rift brewing. Although there have been no traces of an initial confrontation between the duo, Ubi Franklin has been in the news recently after calling out comedian Bovi for cracking jokes about his son. Timaya, recently cleared the air after being accused of a hit and run situation. He now took to his Twitter to issue a warning to Ubi Franklin, telling him he might beat the music executive again if he doesn’t face his job. He tweeted: “Ubi Franklin, you remember the beating I gave you in January last year? Don’t let me beat you again, and pls I like your new JOB. “As Ifeanyi’s[Davido’s son] nanny and please don’t mess it up. Davido is a good guy he can make your life. Please focus on your new JOB. Thanks,” the singer tweeted.